import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
    sns.lineplot(x='date', y='price', data=data, ci=None, color='blue')
    plt.title('What is the average price of stocks over the years?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Year')
    plt.ylabel('Price')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

```
import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='price', kde=True, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['price'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f'Mean: {data["price"].mean():.2f}')
    plt.axvline(data['price'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f'Median: {data["price"].median():.2f}')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of stock prices?')
    plt.xlabel('Price')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

```
import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.sort_values(by='price', ascending=False)
    sns.barplot(x='symbol', y='price', data=data, palette='Blues_d')
    plt.axhline(y=data['price'].max(), color='r', linestyle='--', label=f'Max Price: {data["price"].max():.2f}')
    plt.legend()
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.title('Which stock had the highest price?')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.pivot_table(index='date', columns='symbol', values='price')
    sns.scatterplot(data=data, x='GOOG', y='IBM', color='red', label='GOOG vs IBM')
    sns.scatterplot(data=data, x='GOOG', y='AMZN', color='blue', label='GOOG vs AMZN')
    sns.scatterplot(data=data, x='IBM', y='AMZN', color='green', label='IBM vs AMZN')
    plt.title('What is the correlation between stock prices of different companies?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.groupby('symbol').mean().reset_index()
    sns.barplot(x='symbol', y='price', data=data, palette='Blues_d')
    plt.title('What is the average price of each stock?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Stock Symbol')
    plt.ylabel('Average Price')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
